---
id: org.dxos.introspect
name: Introspect
version: 0.1.0
---

Indexes the DXOS monorepo and exposes packages and exported symbols as plain
serializable data. Phase 1: package walking + symbol extraction. Plugins,
surfaces, capabilities, schemas, idioms, composition queries, and file
watching are deferred to later phases.

## Extensions

| Term      | URI                          |
| --------- | ---------------------------- |
| `type`    | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`      |
| `op`      | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`        |
| `service` | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`   |
| `feat`    | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`      |
| `test`    | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`      |

## Types

```mdl
type SymbolKind
  literals: function | class | interface | type | enum | variable | namespace | unknown
```

```mdl
type Package
  fields:
    name:        string
    version:     string
    private:     boolean
    path:        string                    # relative to the monorepo root
    description?: string
```

```mdl
type PackageDetail
  extends: [Package]
  fields:
    workspaceDependencies: string[]        # `workspace:*` deps
    externalDependencies:  string[]        # catalog or pinned deps
    entryPoints:           string[]        # resolved from exports['.'].source / main
    exportCount:           number
```

```mdl
type SymbolMatch
  fields:
    ref:      string                       # @pkg#name
    package:  string
    name:     string
    kind:     SymbolKind
    summary?: string                       # first line of JSDoc
```

```mdl
type SymbolDetail
  extends: [SymbolMatch]
  fields:
    signature: string
    jsdoc?:    string
    location:  { file: string, line: number, column: number }
    source?:   string                       # only when include=['source']
```

## Services

```mdl
service Introspector
  desc: |
    In-process index of the monorepo. Built lazily — `ready` resolves once
    the package list is loaded; symbols extract on first access per package
    and cache.
  loading: eager
  ops:
    listPackages(filter?: PackageFilter) → Package[]
    getPackage(name: string) → PackageDetail | null
    findSymbol(query: string, kind?: SymbolKind) → SymbolMatch[]
    getSymbol(ref: string, include?: SymbolInclude[]) → SymbolDetail | null
    dispose() → void
```

## Operations

```mdl
op discoverPackages
  desc: |
    Walk the monorepo and return its packages. Tries `moon query projects`
    first; falls back to globbing `packages/**/package.json`. The Moon path
    is gated on `<root>/.moon/` existing so callers running against fixture
    trees don't accidentally pick up a parent monorepo's project graph.
  input:
    monorepoRoot: string
  output: PackageDetail[]
  effects: [fs:read, exec]
```

```mdl
op extractSymbols
  desc: |
    Walk every `.ts/.tsx` file in a package's `src/` and collect exported
    declarations. Merged declarations under one name (e.g. ECHO's
    `export const X` + `export interface X` companion) are surfaced as a
    single symbol whose `source` concatenates both forms.
  input:
    monorepoRoot: string
    pkg: PackageDetail
  output: SymbolMatch[]
  effects: [fs:read]
```

```mdl
op findSymbol
  desc: Locate exported symbols by name or partial name across all packages.
  input:
    query: string
    kind?: SymbolKind
  output: SymbolMatch[]
  note: |
    Ranking: exact match → prefix match → substring. Stable sort by name
    then package within each tier. Capped at 50 results.
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Package indexing

  req F-1.1:
    when: introspector is created against a monorepo with a `.moon/` directory
    then: package list is sourced from `moon query projects`

  req F-1.2:
    when: the monorepo has no Moon workspace
    then: package list is sourced from globbing `packages/**/package.json`

  req F-1.3:
    when: a package has a workspace dependency (`"workspace:*"`)
    then: it appears in `PackageDetail.workspaceDependencies`, not `externalDependencies`
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Symbol extraction

  req F-2.1:
    when: a package's source contains both `export const X` and `export interface X`
    then: a single symbol named `X` is returned whose `source` includes both declarations

  req F-2.2:
    when: a barrel re-exports symbols via `export * as Ns from './Ns'`
    then: the original declarations remain queryable at their source locations
    note: dedup by name prefers concrete declarations over namespace re-exports

  req F-2.3:
    when: `findSymbol(query)` returns no exact match
    then: prefix matches and substring matches follow, in that order

  req F-2.4:
    when: `getSymbol(ref)` is called with `include=['source']`
    then: response carries the full declaration text, otherwise only the signature
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Stable refs

  req F-3.1:
    when: any symbol is returned
    then: it carries a string `ref` of the form `<package>#<name>`

  req F-3.2:
    when: a ref is round-tripped through `parseRef` and `formatSymbolRef`
    then: the original string is recovered exactly
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: Discover fixture packages
  given: introspector created against the fixture monorepo
  when: caller invokes listPackages()
  then:
    - returned names include `@fixture/pkg-a` and `@fixture/pkg-b`
    - `@fixture/pkg-a` is private; `@fixture/pkg-b` is not
```

```mdl
test T-2: Find an ECHO Task by name
  given: introspector ready
  when: caller invokes findSymbol('Task')
  then:
    - a match exists with ref `@fixture/pkg-a#Task`
    - its summary contains `Task item`
```

```mdl
test T-3: Get full source of a merged Schema declaration
  given: introspector ready
  when: caller invokes getSymbol('@fixture/pkg-a#Task', ['source'])
  then:
    - source contains `Schema.Struct`
    - source contains `Type.object`
    - source contains `LabelAnnotation.set(['title'])`
    - source contains both `export const Task` and `export interface Task extends Schema.Schema.Type<typeof Task>`
```

```mdl
test T-4: Resolve symbol location through barrels
  given: pkg-a barrels via `export * as Task from './Task'`
  when: caller invokes getSymbol('@fixture/pkg-a#Task')
  then: location.file ends with `pkg-a/src/Task.ts`
```

